    <completion-notes>
Wave 21 (2026-06-22). Authored cross-cutting MembershipEventPublisher infrastructure for FR-2P2.6 fire-and-forget event publishing, plus matter cluster wiring per event-source-inventory §3A.

Files created (5 src + 1 test):
- Services/Ai/Membership/Events/IMembershipEventPublisher.cs — fire-and-forget contract (PublishAsync NEVER throws)
- Services/Ai/Membership/Events/MembershipEventPublisher.cs — real impl; per-call sender; JSON via canonical SerializerOptions; CorrelationId on envelope + ApplicationProperties (schemaVersion/mutationType/entityLogicalName)
- Services/Ai/Membership/Events/NullMembershipEventPublisher.cs — ADR-032 P2 Quiet no-op peer; logs Information + returns
- Services/Ai/Membership/Events/MembershipEventPublisherOptions.cs — Enabled (default false) + TopicName (default sprk-membership-changes per D3)
- Infrastructure/DI/MembershipModule.cs — SYMMETRIC ADR-032 registration: real when Enabled=true, Null when false
- tests/Services/Ai/Membership/Events/MembershipEventPublisherTests.cs — 10 unit tests (transport failure swallowed; correlationId preserved; serialization canonical; null-peer behavior)

Matter cluster wired (per inventory §3A): Office QuickCreate matter endpoint publishes Added event for implicit ownerid Lookup. Fire-and-forget via discard (_ = publisher.PublishAsync(...)) — 201 Created NOT blocked by Service Bus latency; mutation succeeds even on publish failure (Q2).

NFR-08 (correlationId) wired through endpoint traceId → MembershipChangedEvent.CorrelationId → ServiceBusMessage.CorrelationId + payload.

Operator-deploy gap: task 071 still blocked-operator. Default Membership:EventPublisher:Enabled=false registers Null peer — NO Azure dependency runtime today. Operator flips flag AFTER topic provisioned per task 071 runbook.

Cross-cutting: publisher infrastructure ready for reuse by sibling tasks 082 (document/event cluster) + 083 (task/opportunity cluster — empty per inventory §3D/E).

Tests: 10/10 new pass. Full BFF test suite zero regressions.
Build: 0 errors / 16 warnings (no new).
Publish: 44.89 MB (+0.01 vs 44.88 Wave 20 baseline; well under 60 MB ceiling).
CVE: no new HIGH (pre-existing Kiota CVE unrelated).
ADR-032 binding satisfied — Null-Object peer mandatory for topic-gated state.

Parallel coordination with sibling 084 (MembershipJunctionUpdater consumer): NO file overlap; 081 owns Events/* + Membership:EventPublisher:* config; 084 owns MembershipJunctionUpdater* + Membership:JunctionUpdater:* config; both sections coexist in MembershipModule.cs.
